azure networking lives in single region

networking:  Vnet ---> subnet ---> vm
external load balancer will expose to vm to outsideworld
internal LB , app gateway
Network security group(NSG , rule based firewall) for incoming and outgoing traffic
VPN/expresee route gateway --> to connect to private or another region

Vnet:
    Logical isolation of network segment
    create subnet and isolate traffic using Network security group(NSG)
    provide larger CIDR /16,
    Vnet support static and dynamic ip allocation but recommended is dyanamic,
    support for internal load balancer
    support for dns( azure provide default dns for resource ,but  u can use your own dns)
    support for 


